Text:
As Alpha is looking over documents in her office,
she suddenly looks up and frowns.
Counterfeits...?

Yes, amongst the MCA's currency... We've identified
them in various stores throughout the capital.

Our decision to freely accept their banknotes really
paid off, didn't it?

Although our initial intention was to undermine the
credibility of their currency...
How much is in circulation?
Not much, for now.

The customers who paid with it didn't recognize they
were counterfeits, and it's hard to pinpoint where
they were brought into circulation.
Does the MCA know?

Not yet, it seems. They are recklessly attempting to
increase the number of bills being issued.

Make them aware of it. It will be a major crisis if
the existence of counterfeit bills becomes known
among the citizens.

If doubts arise about the value of the bills,
we won't get away unscathed, either...
Alpha's eyes widen for a moment.
Wait... Was that always the plan?

Intentionally causing a credit collapse... But that
seems self-destructive...
Lady Alpha?

It's nothing. Investigate the source of the
counterfeit money. That's our top priority.
Right! Understood.

After Gamma bows and exits, Alpha turns her gaze
toward the window.
If it wasn't just to make a quick profit...
Then who's behind it, and for what purpose?
Counterfeits? Is that what you're telling me?

Yes, sir. One of the shop staff in our own store
noticed it...
Humph...
Which one?
Huh?
Ah, well, of course...
It's the more poorly made one...I believe?
Hm...
Well, fine. Find out where they're coming from.
Y‑Yes, sir! At once!
Garter quickly rushes out of the room.

The circulation of our bills has already exceeded the
total assets of the MCA, which provided the initial
funding.
The same should hold true for Mitsugoshi...

The only thing currently ensuring the value of our
bills is the vague notion of "trust" among the
uninformed citizens.

Counterfeit money—it looks the same, but unlike
genuine bills, its value is not assured. Essentially,
it's just worthless paper.

If the existence of these counterfeits were to become
known, citizens would collectively start to question
them.

They might even begin to doubt whether the genuine
bills in their wallets are truly valuable...

Such thoughts, that sense of uncertainty, would be
sufficient to erode trust in our currency.
The credit crisis will spread like wildfire.

That's why it was crucial for us to personally
circulate the counterfeit bills...

Intentionally cause a collapse of trust, not only
within the MCA but also one that affects the
troublesome Mitsugoshi. That was the plan handed down
by the Cult.

However, it was meant to occur after we reclaimed all
of the Cult's hidden assets within the MCA.

These assets are concealed among the holdings of
various public companies and organizations...
Recovering them would demand time and effort.
Weren't they aware of that when devising this plan?

By simply standing by and watching as counterfeit
bills continue to circulate, the Cult stands to lose
a substantial amount of assets...

If that was what the Cult's leadership had decided,
then Gettan has no choice but to follow along.
Still, though, they could have at least told him.
What the hell...is going on?
The scars on his eyelids throb painfully.
I'll confirm our objective.
We learned that the counterfeit bills in question

were smuggled aboard this train's cargo when it
departed from the Lawless City.

The search for the manufacturer has been delegated to
another team. Our objective is to recover the actual
goods.

No. 666, you can't act on your own, got it? As your
squad leader, I need to know you're going to follow
my orders.
I know.

Clearly you don't, or we wouldn't need to have this
conversation. You rushed off on your own last time
and the time before. What're you in such a hurry for?
I'm just... It's nothing...
Hehehe... *gulp*

See, you're always trying to shoulder everything on
your own. I won't know what's going on in your head
unless you tell me.

Come on, both of you. Maybe it'd be best if we just
focused on the mission.

Right—wait, you were eating something just now,
weren't you?!
Nooope.

You did. You totally did. I told you not eat on the
mission—
No. 664 sighs.

No. 664 knows just how important their mission is.
That is precisely why she's so worried.

For one, No. 666 is rushing things. Now, everyone
knows how strong she is, and it's thanks in large
part to her that their squad is regarded so highly.

Recently, though, her habit of acting on her own has
started to become intolerable.

No. 664 doesn’t know what's gotten her so riled up,
but at this rate, she’s bound to eventually make some
major blunder.

In this world, there are some screwups that just
can't be fixed. Given the kinds of missions they
go on, a single mistake can easily prove fatal...

As she starts concentrating again, No. 664 prays
they'll be able to complete their mission without
anything going wrong.
There aren't any passengers.
It's a transport train carrying prohibited goods.
That's not surprising...
But why aren't there any guards as well...?
*gasp*
You two!
Agh!
Eeep!
No. 664 and No. 665 are strung up by something.
Now then.
*gasp*

Turning toward the voice they see a man in a suit,
his hair parted to the sides, wearing some sort of
inorganic mask.
May I see your tickets?

The man is empty-handed. He isn't holding a single
weapon.

When they strain their eyes, though, they can make
out the wires surrounding him reflecting in the
light.

They drift freely through the air, as if they have
a will of their own.
Enough with the jokes!
I'll make easy work of you!
Huh?!
They're...pretty tough!
Wires reinforced with magic...!
Who are you?!
John Smith.
